</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[188,1398,1517,1579]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
The name of the new species, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña" authorityYear="2021" box="[536,757,1517,1543]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Leptoplanidae" genus="Parviplana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="sodade">
<emphasis box="[536,757,1517,1543]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Parviplana sodade</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, comes from ‘sodade’ the 
<collectingRegion box="[1064,1124,1518,1544]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Cape</collectingRegion>
Verdean expression for saudade and regional song with rhythms of ‘coladeira’.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
