<subSubSection lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="20" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[189,334,1835,1861]" box="[189,334,1835,1861]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,334,1835,1861]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,334,1835,1861]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[188,1399,1882,2014]" lastBlockId="19.[189,1399,265,432]" lastPageId="19" lastPageNumber="20" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
BODY. Shape oval elongated. Length 
<quantity box="[639,725,1882,1909]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" unit="cm" value="0.8">0.8 cm</quantity>
. Smooth dorsal surface. Background pigmentation light white, transparent where the intestinal braches can be appreciated (
<figureCitation box="[967,1036,1917,1944]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[189,232,1750,1776]" captionTargetBox="[199,1391,940,1708]" captionTargetId="figure-199@20.[189,1399,930,1713]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 4. A–C. Parviplana sodade sp. nov. (MNCN 4.01/2699 to 2708). A. Whole live animal, dorsal view. B. Anterior region with eyes cluster and tentacles (white arrows). C. Histological cross sections of male and female copulatory organ stained with AZAN and sagittal reconstruction of the reproductive system. – D–H. Euplana claridade sp. nov. (MNCN 4.01/2709 to 2718). D. Whole live animal, dorsal view. E. Anterior region with cerebral eyes cluster and tentacles (white arrows). F. Histological section of female copulatory organ stained with AZAN. G. Histological section of male copulatory organ stained with AZAN. H. Sagittal reconstruction of reproductive system. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561535" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561535/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
A–B). Four clusters of cerebral eyes, two anterior with few eyes and more elongated than the posterior two. In sum around 50 cerebral eyes (
<figureCitation box="[257,349,1988,2014]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[189,232,1750,1776]" captionTargetBox="[199,1391,940,1708]" captionTargetId="figure-199@20.[189,1399,930,1713]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 4. A–C. Parviplana sodade sp. nov. (MNCN 4.01/2699 to 2708). A. Whole live animal, dorsal view. B. Anterior region with eyes cluster and tentacles (white arrows). C. Histological cross sections of male and female copulatory organ stained with AZAN and sagittal reconstruction of the reproductive system. – D–H. Euplana claridade sp. nov. (MNCN 4.01/2709 to 2718). D. Whole live animal, dorsal view. E. Anterior region with cerebral eyes cluster and tentacles (white arrows). F. Histological section of female copulatory organ stained with AZAN. G. Histological section of male copulatory organ stained with AZAN. H. Sagittal reconstruction of reproductive system. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561535" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561535/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Fig. 4B</figureCitation>
). Ruffled pharynx. Male and female genital pores located in the posterior half of the body. MALE REPRODUCTIVE SYSTEM. Directed backwards and with a dorso-ventrally oriented penis papilla. With elongated prostatic vesicle, tall granular lining included in the muscular penis bulb (
<figureCitation box="[1240,1333,300,326]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[189,232,1750,1776]" captionTargetBox="[199,1391,940,1708]" captionTargetId="figure-199@20.[189,1399,930,1713]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 4. A–C. Parviplana sodade sp. nov. (MNCN 4.01/2699 to 2708). A. Whole live animal, dorsal view. B. Anterior region with eyes cluster and tentacles (white arrows). C. Histological cross sections of male and female copulatory organ stained with AZAN and sagittal reconstruction of the reproductive system. – D–H. Euplana claridade sp. nov. (MNCN 4.01/2709 to 2718). D. Whole live animal, dorsal view. E. Anterior region with cerebral eyes cluster and tentacles (white arrows). F. Histological section of female copulatory organ stained with AZAN. G. Histological section of male copulatory organ stained with AZAN. H. Sagittal reconstruction of reproductive system. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561535" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561535/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). The 
<emphasis box="[189,368,335,361]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">vasa deferentia</emphasis>
enter the seminal vesicle separately. Seminal vesicle rounded, below the penis bulb and connected with a sort seminal duct to the prostatic vesicle (
<figureCitation box="[883,976,370,397]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[189,232,1750,1776]" captionTargetBox="[199,1391,940,1708]" captionTargetId="figure-199@20.[189,1399,930,1713]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 4. A–C. Parviplana sodade sp. nov. (MNCN 4.01/2699 to 2708). A. Whole live animal, dorsal view. B. Anterior region with eyes cluster and tentacles (white arrows). C. Histological cross sections of male and female copulatory organ stained with AZAN and sagittal reconstruction of the reproductive system. – D–H. Euplana claridade sp. nov. (MNCN 4.01/2709 to 2718). D. Whole live animal, dorsal view. E. Anterior region with cerebral eyes cluster and tentacles (white arrows). F. Histological section of female copulatory organ stained with AZAN. G. Histological section of male copulatory organ stained with AZAN. H. Sagittal reconstruction of reproductive system. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561535" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561535/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
). The male atrium is small and thin, with an internal fold that surrounds the distal part of the penis bulb like a penis sheath (
<figureCitation box="[1212,1306,406,432]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[189,232,1750,1776]" captionTargetBox="[199,1391,940,1708]" captionTargetId="figure-199@20.[189,1399,930,1713]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 4. A–C. Parviplana sodade sp. nov. (MNCN 4.01/2699 to 2708). A. Whole live animal, dorsal view. B. Anterior region with eyes cluster and tentacles (white arrows). C. Histological cross sections of male and female copulatory organ stained with AZAN and sagittal reconstruction of the reproductive system. – D–H. Euplana claridade sp. nov. (MNCN 4.01/2709 to 2718). D. Whole live animal, dorsal view. E. Anterior region with cerebral eyes cluster and tentacles (white arrows). F. Histological section of female copulatory organ stained with AZAN. G. Histological section of male copulatory organ stained with AZAN. H. Sagittal reconstruction of reproductive system. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561535" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561535/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[189,1398,471,533]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
FEMALE REPRODUCTIVE SYSTEM. With a vagina bulbosa (
<figureCitation box="[841,934,471,497]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="20.[189,232,1750,1776]" captionTargetBox="[199,1391,940,1708]" captionTargetId="figure-199@20.[189,1399,930,1713]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="Fig. 4. A–C. Parviplana sodade sp. nov. (MNCN 4.01/2699 to 2708). A. Whole live animal, dorsal view. B. Anterior region with eyes cluster and tentacles (white arrows). C. Histological cross sections of male and female copulatory organ stained with AZAN and sagittal reconstruction of the reproductive system. – D–H. Euplana claridade sp. nov. (MNCN 4.01/2709 to 2718). D. Whole live animal, dorsal view. E. Anterior region with cerebral eyes cluster and tentacles (white arrows). F. Histological section of female copulatory organ stained with AZAN. G. Histological section of male copulatory organ stained with AZAN. H. Sagittal reconstruction of reproductive system. Abbreviations: see Material and methods." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4561535" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4561535/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Fig. 4C</figureCitation>
) and backwards oriented. Cement and shell glands open in a pouch located within the vaginal complex. Lang’s vesicle present.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="20" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[189,303,572,598]" box="[189,303,572,598]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,572,598]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,572,598]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[189,1400,618,715]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicName authority="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña, 2021" authorityName="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,413,618,644]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Leptoplanidae" genus="Parviplana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="sodade" status="sp. nov">
<emphasis box="[189,413,618,644]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Parviplana sodade</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[422,509,619,645]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" rank="species">sp. nov</taxonomicNameLabel>
belongs to the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hyman" authorityYear="1953" box="[774,906,618,644]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Leptoplanidae" genus="Parviplana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[774,906,618,644]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Parviplana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the absence of tentacles, presence of seminal vesicle, and prostatic vesicle with a tall granular lining with prostatic functions. Female apparatus with vagina bulbosa and Lang´s vesicle.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[188,1399,754,851]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hyman" authorityYear="1953" box="[189,321,754,780]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Leptoplanidae" genus="Parviplana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[189,321,754,780]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Parviplana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comprises 3 species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Faubel, 1983" authorityName="Faubel" authorityYear="1983" box="[573,849,754,780]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Leptoplanidae" genus="Parviplana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="hymani">
<emphasis box="[573,687,754,780]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. hymani</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Faubel A." box="[694,849,754,780]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" pagination="17 - 121" refId="ref16910" refString="Faubel A. 1983. The Polycladida, Turbellaria; Proposal and establishment of a new system. Part I. The Acotylea. Mitteilungen aus dem Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museum und Institut 80: 17 - 121." type="journal article" year="1983">Faubel, 1983</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Perez-Garcia, Norena &amp; Cervera, 2018" authorityName="Perez-Garcia, Norena &amp; Cervera" authorityYear="2018" class="Rhabditophora" family="Leptoplanidae" genus="Parviplana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="jeronimoi">
<emphasis box="[860,1001,755,780]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. jeronimoi</emphasis>
Pérez-García, Noreña &amp; Cervera, 2018
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Du Bois-Reymond Marcus, 1958)" baseAuthorityName="Du Bois-Reymond Marcus" baseAuthorityYear="1958" box="[317,861,789,816]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Leptoplanidae" genus="Parviplana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="lynca">
<emphasis box="[317,416,789,815]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. lynca</emphasis>
(Du Bois-Reymond Marcus, 1958)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Du Bois-Reymond Marcus" baseAuthorityYear="1958" box="[878,1088,789,815]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Leptoplanidae" genus="Parviplana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="lynca">
<emphasis box="[878,1088,789,815]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Parviplana lynca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be easy and clearly distinguished from the other two species by the presence of nuchal tentacles, exclusive of this species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[189,1398,890,952]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Faubel" authorityYear="1983" box="[189,418,890,916]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Leptoplanidae" genus="Parviplana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="hymani">
<emphasis box="[189,418,890,916]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Parviplana hymani</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña, 2021" authorityName="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña" authorityYear="2021" box="[758,874,890,916]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Leptoplanidae" genus="Parviplana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="sodade" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[758,874,890,916]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. sodade</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[885,983,891,917]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, by the 
<emphasis box="[1087,1235,890,916]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">vas deferens</emphasis>
which opens together into the seminal vesicle, and the prostate vesicle not included into de penis bulb.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="19.[189,1399,991,1193]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">
<taxonomicName authority="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña, 2021" authorityName="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña" authorityYear="2021" box="[189,412,991,1017]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Leptoplanidae" genus="Parviplana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="sodade" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[189,412,991,1017]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Parviplana sodade</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[420,512,991,1017]" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
possesses more similarities with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perez-Garcia, Norena &amp; Cervera" authorityYear="2018" box="[908,1049,991,1016]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Leptoplanidae" genus="Parviplana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="jeronimoi">
<emphasis box="[908,1049,991,1016]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. jeronimoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Both species share the penis sheath and more than 25 cerebral eyes, but clear differences separate them. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perez-Garcia, Norena &amp; Cervera" authorityYear="2018" box="[1079,1331,1026,1052]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Leptoplanidae" genus="Parviplana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="jeronimoi">
<emphasis box="[1079,1331,1026,1052]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Parviplana jeronimoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a fleshy appearance and amber pigmentation. The size is also noticeable different, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perez-Garcia, Norena &amp; Cervera" authorityYear="2018" box="[1137,1279,1062,1087]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Leptoplanidae" genus="Parviplana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="jeronimoi">
<emphasis box="[1137,1279,1062,1087]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. jeronimoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can reach lengths of 
<quantity box="[313,399,1096,1123]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="20.0">20 mm</quantity>
, while 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña" authorityYear="2021" box="[483,595,1096,1122]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Leptoplanidae" genus="Parviplana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="sodade">
<emphasis box="[483,595,1096,1122]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. sodade</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in full mature state does not reach 
<quantity box="[1009,1080,1096,1123]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" unit="mm" value="8.0">8 mm</quantity>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Perez-Garcia, Norena &amp; Cervera" authorityYear="2018" box="[1091,1344,1096,1122]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Leptoplanidae" genus="Parviplana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="jeronimoi">
<emphasis box="[1091,1344,1096,1122]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">Parviplana jeronimoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also presents 
<emphasis box="[293,472,1131,1157]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">vasa deferentia</emphasis>
joined in a single 
<emphasis box="[688,833,1131,1157]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">vas deferens</emphasis>
, a small female atrium and a corrugated surface between the two genital pores, characteristics not present in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Cuadrado &amp; Rodríguez &amp; Moro &amp; Grande &amp; Noreña" authorityYear="2021" box="[896,1008,1167,1193]" class="Rhabditophora" family="Leptoplanidae" genus="Parviplana" kingdom="Animalia" order="Polycladida" pageId="19" pageNumber="20" phylum="Platyhelminthes" rank="species" species="sodade">
<emphasis box="[896,1008,1167,1193]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="20">P. sodade</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
